722577f-b.text:
(1)
Pike Street, west side, north from but not including Madison, to, but not including Henry Streets. The view shows a Synagogue, The Congcegation Aushei Slulsk, at No, 34 Pike Street.
NE6 27o8  July 25, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, showing a closer view of 36 to 32 Pike Street, west side, between Madison and Henry Streets. 34 Pike Street is the
Synagogue of the Congregation Anshei Slulsk.
October 28, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
(3) The samo, as No. 1, shoiwng a closer view of Nos. 26-28 Pike Stree., at and adjoining the S.W. corner of Henry Street.
N2E6. 2509  July 2S, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
